  "brief_justification": "Theoretical essay in International Political Economy analyzing Benjamin Cohen's intellectual trajectory regarding global political order, structural power, and the tension between realism and Keynesianism. No empirical data analysis of any kind; the paper is an interpretive intellectual history with normative arguments about the decline of Keynesianism and its implications for liberal democracy. Implicit causal claims appear in arguments about Keynesianism's decline provoking anti-democratic outcomes (a Polanyian 'double movement')."
